op-keysync (1.1.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add prerm script — kills running instance on upgrade/remove so the
    old version does not keep running after apt upgrade. Does not restart
    it (op-keysync requires user session context; autostart handles relaunch
    on next login).

 -- op-keysync maintainer <noreply@github.com>  Thu, 20 Mar 2026 09:00:00 +0100

op-keysync (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Silence non-error notifications — only sync failures and missing
    dependency warnings are shown. State changes (lock, unlock, sync OK,
    clipboard copy) are silent and reflected in the tray icon only.
  * Fix tray icon flash — skip set_icon_full() when icon is unchanged.
  * Fix dock flash on wl-copy — strip GIO_LAUNCHED_DESKTOP_FILE from
    subprocess environment so GNOME does not show wl-copy in the dock.
  * Add startup dependency check with tray menu warnings for missing tools.
  * Thread safety — RLock protecting secrets between GTK and socket threads.
  * Fix _do_unlock UI — tray updates immediately on unlock, not after sync.

 -- op-keysync maintainer <noreply@github.com>  Thu, 19 Mar 2026 09:00:00 +0100

op-keysync (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * GNOME tray app for syncing 1Password API keys to shell sessions.
  * Automatic purge on screen lock and idle timeout.
  * Shell hook for bash and zsh.

 -- op-keysync maintainer <noreply@github.com>  Wed, 18 Mar 2026 17:17:19 +0100
